{"word":"G4521 - σάββατον - sábbaton - sab'-bat-on - Sabbath","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σάββατον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong>sábbaton"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong>sab'-bat-on"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong>Sabbath"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"ஓய்வுநாள், வாரம் - பால் வேறுபாடற்ற பெயர்ச்சொல்"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"1. the seventh day of each week, sabbath"},{"paragraph":"2. seven days, a week"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>Part(s) of speech:</strong> Noun Neuter / பெயர்ச்சொல் (அஃறிணை)</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English:</strong> Of Hebrew origin [<a href=\"#/H7676 - שַׁבָּת - shabbâth - shab-bawth'/7676\">H7676</a>]; the <i>Sabbath</i> (that is, <i>Shabbath</i>), or day of weekly <i>repose</i> from secular avocations (also the observance or institution itself); by extension a <i>se'nnight</i>, that is, the interval between two Sabbaths; likewise the plural in all the above applications: - sabbath (day), week."},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"spacer\"></span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4520 - σαββατισμός - sabbatismós - sab-bat-is-mos'/4520\">G4520</a>, <a href=\"#/G4521 - σάββατον - sábbaton - sab'-bat-on/4521\">G4521</a>"}]}